<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  AUTHORITATIVE real CargoWise Organization export (client-supplied, DELFFRATI).
  Use this as the ground-truth structure for the XML generator and the field contract.
  Key facts this sample establishes (differ from the earlier hand-written template):
    * Root is <Native ... version="2.0"> DIRECTLY - NOT wrapped in UniversalInterchange.
    * Namespace is http://www.cargowise.com/Schemas/Native/2011/11  (note the /2011/11).
    * Header carries <OwnerCode> + <EnableCodeMapping> (and OverrideAdditionalAddressInformation lives on OrgHeader).
    * EVERY entity has a <PK> GUID and Action="MERGE". On import you may omit PK to let CW match by Code;
      keep Action="MERGE" for insert-or-update.
    * Role flag is <IsAirLine> (capital L), and there are user flags IsUserFlag1..32.
    * OrgContact uses <ContactName> + <Title> (not Name/JobTitle); Gender 'N', NotifyMode 'DND' are valid.
    * Reference lookups use TableName + inner <Code> (+ optional <PK>): CountryCode/RefCountry,
      RelatedPortCode/RefUNLOCO, ClosestPort/RefUNLOCO, GlbCompany, ARDebtorGroup/OrgDebtorGroup,
      APCreditorGroup/OrgCreditorGroup, currencies/RefCurrency.
    * OrgCompanyDataCollection holds ONE OrgCompanyData per GL company (here PAR and MNL).
    * Big optional blocks exist (OrgMiscServ, OrgSupplierBuyerLink_BuyerCollection) - CW fills sensible
      defaults; a minimal import does NOT need to send them.
-->
